UPSTREAM WORK

This project is a derivative work of the CRG Scoreboard overlay,
originally developed by the CRG Scoreboard contributors.

Original project:  CRG Derby Scoreboard
Source repository: https://github.com/rollerderby/scoreboard
License:           GNU General Public License v3 (or later)

The following files in this repository are derived from or substantially
based on files originally distributed as part of the CRG Scoreboard:

  index.html        — derived from CRG overlay HTML
  index.css         — derived from CRG overlay CSS
  index.js          — derived from CRG overlay JavaScript
  admin/index.html  — derived from CRG admin overlay HTML
  admin/index.js    — derived from CRG admin overlay JavaScript
  admin/index.css   — derived from CRG admin overlay CSS

The following files are original works by the Thin Mint Scoreboard Overlay developers
and were not derived from the CRG Scoreboard:

  config.js             — deployment configuration
  loader.js             — CRG connection bootstrap and loader
  test-connection.html  — pre-bout connectivity test page

---

MODIFICATIONS

The following changes were made to the original CRG Scoreboard overlay:

  - Broadcast-style visual restyling of the scoreboard overlay and
    admin panel, inspired by the visual language of network sports graphics
  - Support for connecting to a remote CRG Scoreboard instance
    over a local network, configurable via the admin panel
  - CRG connection settings (IP, port, timeout) synced via CRG WebSocket
    state so all connected overlay clients stay in sync automatically
  - Configurable connection timeout with offline error screen
  - Reconnection badge displayed when WebSocket drops mid-bout
  - Cache-busting on core.js to pick up CRG updates automatically
  - Consolidated connection bootstrap (loader.js)
  - Deployment configuration file (config.js)
  - Pre-bout connection test page (test-connection.html)
  - Score change flash animation and jam-score delta float
  - Winning score color highlight and synchronized glow pulse
  - Jam and period urgency indicators
  - Timeout type styling (Official, Team, Official Review)
  - Synchronized blink/pulse system across all live indicators
  - Smooth panel slide animation keyed to placement mode
  - Jammer panel with lead indicator, star pass, and penalty states
  - Lineup/blocker panel with synchronized penalty blinking
  - Post-timeout lineup clock
  - Game Tab context banner with customizable text and color
  - Bottom Placement mode
  - Winner highlighting on official and unofficial score

